    <note>Guo(1) Youzhi [19498] Wen Tong, WJ, 39.11b-14a. According to Wen(2) Tong [10173], his lineage was a member of the same kindred group (yinjia) and Youzhi's son-in-law, Wen(2) Weiji (not in dataset), was probably kin to Tong. However, the yinjia is also documented by the fact that two of Wen(2) Tong's sons were son-in-laws of Guo(1) Youzhi's son-in-law, Li(2) Tong [19503]--Wen(2) Baoguang [10175] was married to Li(2) Tong's daughter by his second wife, Guo(1) Youzhi's daughter, whereas Wen(2) Chaoguang [10174] was married to Youzhi's daughter by his first wife, born Bao. See documentation for probable uncle, Xipu [19496], for the link between the Huayang Guo(1). After Youzhi failed the metropolitan exams, he returned to Chengdu where he became a very successful teacher. According to Wen(2) Tong, Youzhi's wife, born Yuwen, was from a great Sichuan lineage (daxing). CBD, 3, 2132.</note>
